<topic id="project-validation-and-transformation">
  <title>Batch Validation and Transformation</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Projects<indexterm>Batch validation</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Projects<indexterm>Batch transformations</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Batch validation</indexterm>
        <indexterm>Batch transformation</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p><ph keyref="product"/> provides support for batch validation and batch transformation.
      Actions are available in the <uicontrol product="author developer editor"
        >Project</uicontrol><uicontrol product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
        >Navigator</uicontrol> view that provide the ability to validate or transform one or more
      files attached to a project.</p>
    <section id="batch_validation">
      <title>Batch Validation</title>
      <p>To batch validate files, select the files (or directories), right-click, and choose one of
        the following actions from the <uicontrol>Validate</uicontrol> submenu:</p>
      <p>
        <dl>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/check-well-formedness">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/validate">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/validate-with-schema">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/configure-validation-scenario">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/clear-validation-markers"
            product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
        </dl>
      </p>
    </section>
    <section id="batch_transformation">
      <title>Batch Transformation</title>
      <p>To batch transform files, select the files (or directories), right-click, and choose one of
        the following actions from the <uicontrol>Transform</uicontrol> submenu:</p>
      <p>
        <dl>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/apply-transformation-scenario">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/configure-transformation-scenario">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/transform-with">
            <dt/>
            <dd/>
          </dlentry>
        </dl>
      </p>
    </section>
  </body>
